flowchart TD
  A[Business problem and current state] --> B{Microservices justified?}
  B -- no --> C[Modular monolith or simpler service style]
  B -- yes --> D[Define capabilities and subdomains]
  D --> E[Map commands, queries, and data ownership]
  E --> F{Cross-service transaction?}
  F -- yes --> G[Saga plus outbox plus idempotency]
  F -- no --> H[Local transaction only]
  E --> I{Cross-service query?}
  I -- small and tolerable --> J[API composition]
  I -- frequent or expensive --> K[CQRS or query service]
  E --> L{Client API complexity?}
  L -- single stable entry --> M[API gateway]
  L -- client-specific APIs --> N[BFF]
  G --> O[Contract tests and failure tests]
  H --> O
  J --> O
  K --> O
  M --> O
  N --> O
  O --> P[Health, metrics, logs, traces, audit, runbook]
  P --> Q[Deploy then release with staged traffic and rollback]
  A --> R{Existing monolith?}
  R -- yes --> S[Strangler plus anti-corruption layer]
  S --> E
